author: stevel
msg: This bit of complexity verifies the sha1 key of the m2 library against what is in the libraries file.
Provided the ant distro is validated, this ensures that the maven library that comes down is also valid.

author: carnold
msg: LOGCXX-126: ConsoleAppender now checks fwide and uses C STL IO

author: djencks
msg: Initial work on making version optional on gbean references.  This breaks build around security-builder.  This has plenty of known problems.

author: maxb
msg: Fix use of incorrect byte order in UUID generation. Compatibility concerns are
minimal, as this affects only the generation of new UUIDs.
Neither the binary->string nor string->binary conversions are altered.
* crypto/getuuid.c (apr_uuid_get): Fill in the UUID data in network byte order
